      "content": "i get that, but for a lot of these guys, 'long term' doesn't really matter if they go bust next year trying to pay for all the new gear. it feels like the benefits you're mentioning—like reputation or grants—are kind of speculative compared to the very real, immediate cost of just staying in business. do you think it's fair to say these regs are being pushed more for political optics than actual economic practicality for small businesses?",
